<HL>
   Letters to the Editor:
   It's Always Too Late
</HL>
<DATE>
09/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15
</SO>
<GV>
DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)
</GV>
<LP>
   Your Aug. 28 page-one article on the U.S. military's
ill-preparedness for conflict in the Middle East reminded me
of a quote from "Wolf Willow," a book by Wallace Stegner:
"{M}ost education trains us for the past, as most preparation
for war readies us for the war just over."
   Arlie R. Nogay
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Pittsburgh
</TEXT>
